this up by myself!

10:06.573 --> 10:08.608
It's just some fucking
papers, honey.

10:11.478 --> 10:13.981
God damn it.

10:14.047 --> 10:16.416
The forces
of anti-American hatred

10:16.483 --> 10:18.151
that killed my brother...

10:19.419 --> 10:20.688
those enemies are out

10:20.754 --> 10:22.790
to destroy every
single one of us.

10:22.856 --> 10:25.859
It's one of the reasons
I went into law...

10:25.926 --> 10:28.361
so that I could work
with companies

10:28.428 --> 10:30.430
like Borns Tech,

10:30.497 --> 10:33.166
who make it their mission

10:33.233 --> 10:37.137
to fight evil
in the Middle East.

10:38.438 --> 10:39.506
The evidence will show

10:39.572 --> 10:43.410
that this case is about evil.

10:43.476 --> 10:44.778
Ha!

10:44.845 --> 10:46.446
How'd you get this?

10:46.513 --> 10:48.348
Friends in the IT department.

10:48.415 --> 10:49.458
Listen...
Listen to this part.

10:49.482 --> 10:51.852
In 2004,

10:51.919 --> 10:55.288
my brother Adam was killed

10:55.355 --> 10:58.258
fighting the forces of evil
in Mosul.

10:59.727 --> 11:01.361
I know the Larsons' hurt.

11:01.428 --> 11:07.200
I know what it is
to... lose someone.

11:07.267 --> 11:09.302
- He was...
- See?

11:09.369 --> 11:10.804
That.

11:10.871 --> 11:12.840
That's why he tapped her:

11:12.906 --> 11:15.475
her dead brother.

11:15.542 --> 11:16.643
Can you believe it?

11:16.744 --> 11:18.746
It's not a bad choice.

11:19.980 --> 11:21.614
The jury's going to love her.

11:21.749 --> 11:25.585
That's my opening in my case.

11:25.652 --> 11:27.520
Think about it.

11:27.587 --> 11:28.756
The hardest thing to do

11:28.822 --> 11:30.858
is to humanize
a corporate client,

11:30.924 --> 11:33.426
and Lucy does that.
Look at her.

11:33.493 --> 11:35.095
He was my entire world.

11:39.499 --> 11:41.001
You're right.

11:42.369 --> 11:43.771
I hate that.

11:43.804 --> 11:45.572
And when he died, I vowed...

11:45.638 --> 11:47.040
That's all you get from this?

11:47.107 --> 11:49.276
- ...to make it my mission...
- What?

11:49.342 --> 11:50.443
What?
What did I miss?

11:50.510 --> 11:52.946
...Borns Tech who keep
our loved ones safe.

11:53.013 --> 11:55.015
That it's cruel for Donald

11:55.082 --> 11:56.950
to be putting a young
girl through this,

11:57.017 --> 12:00.020
to be milking her pain
for the good of a case.

12:00.087 --> 12:01.454
When she's done with it,

12:01.521 --> 12:02.598
you think he's going to care?

12:02.622 --> 12:03.622
Of course not.

12:03.656 --> 12:05.192
For all we know,

12:05.258 --> 12:07.460
this is exactly
why he hired her,

12:07.527 --> 12:11.799
just in case Borns Tech
got caught on their shit.

12:11.865 --> 12:14.234
He's so fucking cold.

12:24.344 --> 12:27.347
A little hot to be doing
that today, isn't it, judge?

12:29.883 --> 12:31.627
Did you ever build a float
out of these things

12:31.651 --> 12:34.354
and put them in the Rose Parade?

12:34.421 --> 12:36.456
What are you doing here?

12:36.523 --> 12:37.825
I would have called,

12:37.858 --> 12:39.135
but your clerk wouldn't
give me the number...

12:39.159 --> 12:40.759
- Are you drunk?
- ...so I came over. No.

12:40.828 --> 12:42.505
I hope so for your sake
that you are drunk.

12:42.529 --> 12:45.098
I'm not drinking, no.
This is really important.

12:45.165 --> 12:46.867
If you'll just let me
come inside with you,

12:46.934 --> 12:48.635
I'll explain it to you.

12:48.701 --> 12:50.237
Inside.

12:50.303 --> 12:52.873
- Are you coming?
- Inside, Mr. McBride.

13:00.881 --> 13:02.449
You got two minutes.

13:02.515 --> 13:04.017
All right.

13:04.084 --> 13:07.287
We dug this up
at Ryan Larson's house.

13:07.354 --> 13:08.989
It's a model and some blueprints

13:09.056 --> 13:11.258
for a weapons system
he was working on
for Borns Tech.

13:11.324 --> 13:13.961
Are you trying to get
held in contempt again?

13:14.027 --> 13:15.462
You can get disbarred

13:15.528 --> 13:17.730
for even discussing this
with me outside the court,

13:17.865 --> 13:18.932
let alone argue it.

13:18.999 --> 13:20.467
I'm not arguing anything.

13:20.533 --> 13:23.937
You asked me a question.
I'm just answering it.

13:24.004 --> 13:25.772
See this? I got that

13:25.873 --> 13:27.283
when a guy tried
to run me down today.

13:27.307 --> 13:28.885
That's the same guy
who's been following me

13:28.909 --> 13:30.243
ever since I took the case.

13:31.378 --> 13:32.545
You're insane.

13:32.612 --> 13:33.612
And I'm not...

13:33.646 --> 13:34.882
It gets better.

13:34.915 --> 13:36.516
Somebody broke
in my storage locker.

13:36.583 --> 13:38.085
Dumped out all the discovery,

13:38.151 --> 13:39.987
looking for this fucking
thing, I'm guessing.

13:40.053 --> 13:42.122
Then you report it
to the police.

13:42.189 --> 13:43.523
You don't bring it to me.

13:43.590 --> 13:45.158
I'd love to report it
to the police,

13:45.225 --> 13:46.535
but you see,
the police pulled me over

13:46.559 --> 13:48.728
on a bullshit DUI,
beat the hell out of me,

13:48.795 --> 13:49.796
and tased my daughter.

13:49.897 --> 13:51.531
Then my client gets killed

13:51.598 --> 13:52.900
outside your court.

13:52.933 --> 13:54.334
They still don't have a suspect.

13:54.401 --> 13:57.170
Two of my witnesses get
popped on a drug charge,

13:57.237 --> 13:59.372
Neither one has a record
for drug dealing.

13:59.439 --> 14:01.909
Now, you think all
that's a coincidence?

14:01.942 --> 14:04.444
That's a laundry
list of shit, judge.

14:06.980 --> 14:09.582
What are you looking for
from me, Mr. McBride?

14:09.649 --> 14:10.717
Huh?

14:10.783 --> 14:11.919
My help?

14:11.985 --> 14:13.120
The rules say that the court

14:13.186 --> 14:14.754
has to retain
evidence pre-trial

14:14.821 --> 14:16.389
if the circumstances warrant it.

14:16.456 --> 14:19.126
As long as I tell the other
side what I'm doing,

14:19.192 --> 14:21.328
you have to take this evidence.

14:24.497 --> 14:25.632
We scoured our files,

14:25.698 --> 14:26.967
and we didn't find anything

14:27.034 --> 14:29.269
about what McBride
dug up in Larson's yard.

14:29.336 --> 14:31.939
Is this a Borns Tech
weapon or not?

14:33.306 --> 14:35.775
It's a fair question,
Wendell. Is it?

14:35.842 --> 14:37.777
Is this thing
one of ours or not?

14:37.844 --> 14:40.247
I deny knowing
anything about this.

14:42.682 --> 14:44.184
The firm knows nothing.

14:44.251 --> 14:47.054
Are you all crazy?
We're breaking the law here.

14:48.288 --> 14:50.323
You can pretend we have
plausible deniability,

14:50.390 --> 14:52.960
- but we don't.
- That's exactly what we have.

14:53.026 --> 14:55.228
This case is only about

14:55.295 --> 14:58.365
what caused a boat to blow up
in the middle of the night,

14:58.431 --> 15:02.335
and for that the burden is
completely on the plaintiff.

15:02.402 --> 15:03.770
If you were general counsel,

15:03.836 --> 15:05.572
what would you do
with this information?

15:05.638 --> 15:07.740
Why are you asking me?

15:07.807 --> 15:09.876
First because
you're outside counsel.

15:09.977 --> 15:11.344
We pay for your advice.

15:11.411 --> 15:14.314
Secondly, your opinion
seems to fucking matter...

15:14.381 --> 15:16.249
not to me,
but evidently to them.

15:16.316 --> 15:20.053
I would maintain the client's
privilege of confidentiality.

15:20.120 --> 15:21.988
So you'd stay quiet as a mouse.

15:21.989 --> 15:23.991
I'm not a fucking mouse.

15:25.292 --> 15:27.094
And should McBride have evidence

15:27.160 --> 15:29.996
which shows
we were working up
a band cluster bomb,

15:29.997 --> 15:31.031
you'd still stay quiet?

15:31.098 --> 15:33.000
There's no evidence.

15:33.066 --> 15:34.534
It's just allegations.

15:34.601 --> 15:36.069
Allegations?

15:37.404 --> 15:40.373
Just between us lawyers,
we already know

15:40.440 --> 15:43.043
Borns Tech did bad shit
and covered it up.

15:43.110 --> 15:46.246
The law imposes a duty
on me to report this.

15:46.313 --> 15:48.681
Yeah, and just
between us lawyers,

15:48.748 --> 15:50.050
should somebody report it

15:50.117 --> 15:51.718
outside this firm or Borns Tech,

15:51.784 --> 15:54.254
violating the attorney-
client privilege,

15:54.321 --> 15:57.357
somebody would lose
his law license.

15:57.424 --> 16:00.793
And for staying quiet,
somebody could go to prison.

16:00.860 --> 16:02.362
All right, I've sat here

16:02.429 --> 16:03.896
and listened to this bullshit

16:04.031 --> 16:05.311
just about long...

16:05.365 --> 16:07.934
You've got much to think
about and consider.

16:08.035 --> 16:10.570
Let's all take a break.

16:10.637 --> 16:12.039
Shall we?

16:20.413 --> 16:23.083
Okay, so, assuming
we get to trial,

16:23.150 --> 16:25.752
Ned is our only expert witness.

16:25.818 --> 16:26.919
So what else?

16:27.054 --> 16:28.355
What else?

16:28.421 --> 16:31.424
It's better to have one
than none, isn't it?

16:31.491 --> 16:33.560
It's not how many
witnesses you have,

16:33.626 --> 16:35.662
it's what they have
to say that counts.

16:35.728 --> 16:38.398
Then we're really fucked
because Ned is Ned,

16:38.465 --> 16:40.133
and the jury's
already going to hate him

16:40.200 --> 16:41.301
for the revenge porn.

16:41.368 --> 16:43.103
We may have another witness.

16:43.170 --> 16:44.604
- Who?
- Right?

16:44.671 --> 16:46.106
We don't have him yet.

16:46.173 --> 16:47.974
We're going to have him.

16:48.075 --> 16:50.543
I'll see to it if you don't.

16:56.249 --> 16:57.417
Are you drunk?

16:57.484 --> 17:00.520
That's none of your
goddamn business.

17:01.821 --> 17:03.723
You... You see this, right?

17:06.159 --> 17:07.794
Everyone's here because of you,

17:07.859 --> 17:10.097
so it is my goddamn business.

17:10.163 --> 17:12.432
When I asked you point blank

17:12.499 --> 17:13.942
if I should be scared
to do this case,

17:13.965 --> 17:15.167
you said no.

17:15.234 --> 17:17.569
Well, I'll let
you girls sit here

17:17.637 --> 17:20.573
and dwell on your
fucking problems.

